## GET /api/notifications

Scenarios 26 (own) and 27 (admin, any account).

Request (Alice, her own history — newest first):
```json
GET /api/notifications
Authorization: Bearer <jwt for Alice>
```

Response — 200 OK:
```json
{
  "items": [
    {
      "id": "40000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000002",
      "orderId": "20000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001",
      "type": "ORDER_CANCELLED",
      "message": "Your order has been cancelled.",
      "createdAt": "2026-07-13T15:00:01Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "40000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001",
      "orderId": "20000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001",
      "type": "ORDER_PLACED",
      "message": "Your order has been placed.",
      "createdAt": "2026-07-13T14:00:01Z"
    }
  ],
  "total": 2
}
```

Request (Administrator, support lookup for Bilal — NTF-003):
```json
GET /api/notifications?accountId=bbbbbbbb-bbbb-4bbb-8bbb-bbbbbbbbbbbb
Authorization: Bearer <jwt for admin>
```

Response — 200 OK (empty — scenario 17/Database-Scripts step 18 already
proved Bilal's rejected checkout produced no order and therefore no
event; NTF-001 only fires on a successfully placed order):
```json
{
  "items": [],
  "total": 0
}
```

A Customer passing `?accountId=` for anyone but themselves gets 403
(NTF-003), same posture as Phase 5's `?customerId=` on GET /api/orders.

