## Regression check against Phases 1–6

- Placing and cancelling an order (Phases 5, 6) must still succeed even if
  this service is entirely down — verify by stopping notification-service
  and repeating Phase 5/6's happy-path requests; the 201/200 responses
  must be identical, and no order/order_items row anywhere depends on this
  service being reachable (NTF-005, and the "database-per-service, no
  coupling" principle from Archive/Development/Database §0).
- Once notification-service is back up and the queued events are consumed
  (or, if using a dead-letter path, manually replayed), GET
  /api/notifications must reflect exactly the events that were missed —
  no duplicates, nothing lost.
